The paper deals with the capacity-memory tradeoff in broadcast channels with cache memories, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The use of cache memories also involves networked communication (cs.NI) and distributed systems (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the optimization of cache sizes, which can be seen as a machine learning problem (cs.LG) or a signal processing problem (cs.SI).
